About SushiSwap (SUSHI)

SushiSwap is a decentralized exchange (DEX), launched in August 2020 by a pseudonymous developer named Chef Nomi. Its native cryptocurrency is called SUSHI, an ERC-20 token. 
SushiSwap DEX was deployed on Ethereum as a software fork of Uniswap. A ‘Uniswap fork’ mean SushiSwap’s developers utilized a modified version of the open-source code of Uniswap to build the DEX. 
SushiSwap now operates on over 25 blockchain networks, including Ethereum, Linea, Optimism, Polygon, BNB Chain, and more. SushiSwap has also expanded beyond its initial trading tools to feature: Kashi for lending, MISO for token launchpad services, and BentoBox for yield optimization. 
Today, the main use cases of SUSHI token are for governance, staking, reward, and yield farming. SUSHI holders are typically active DeFi traders and long-term crypto investors.

  • How do I add SushiSwap to MetaMask?

    MetaMask automatically displays popular tokens like SushiSwap（SUSHI）within your wallet. If you are not seeing your SUSHI in MetaMask, you can manually add it using the "Add to MetaMask" button above, over the price chart. Please remember that you first need to install MetaMask extension if you are on a PC or Mac (desktop computer). If you are on mobile, please check out our MetaMask Support guide here for more info.

  • What is the price of SushiSwap today?

  • How do I buy SushiSwap?

    Buying SushiSwap (SUSHI) in MetaMask wallet is speedy, simple, and safe. You can buy SushiSwap (SUSHI) tokens directly in MetaMask using payment methods like a credit card, debit card, bank account, Apple Pay, Google Pay, or PayPal. There's no need for centralised exchanges. Select from thousands of your favourite tokens to buy on over 15 networks including Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain, Linea, Base, and more.

  • What is SUSHIx?

    SUSHIx, sometimes written as xSUSHI, is a token that you receive when you stake SUSHI on SushiSwap—aka staking on the SushiBar. Initially, the SUSHI you stake is pegged 1:1 with the SUSHIx you receive. Over time,  your SUSHIx will grow as it accumulates compound earnings. You can unstake SUSHIx at any time; there is no lockup period.

    Swapping SUSHI is simple and cost-effective with MetaMask. Choose from thousands of your favourite tokens across ten networks including Ethereum, Solana, Linea, Base, and Arbitrum. MetaMask Swaps also include gas fees right in your quotes, making swapping crypto as smooth as can be.

  • How do I bridge SushiSwap?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging SushiSwap (SUSHI) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging SUSHI from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap SUSHI from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What can you do with SushiSwap?

    With SushiSwap, you can send and receive SUSHI, the network's native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. SUSHI is supported in decentralised apps for trading, staking, yield optimisation, and payments. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use SUSHI in select web3 financial strategies, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.

  • How do I trade SushiSwap for other cryptocurrencies?

    Trading SushiSwap (SUSHI) for ETH, WBTC, or SOL can be done directly in MetaMask. For more information on how to swap SUSHI, head to MetaMask Support.
